    "## 1. Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "### Problem Statement\n",
    "Image processing is a fundamental application of linear algebra and array operations. Every digital image is essentially a matrix (2D array) where each element represents pixel intensity. Understanding how to manipulate these arrays is crucial for:\n",
    "- Computer vision and image recognition\n",
    "- Data augmentation in deep learning\n",
    "- Medical imaging analysis\n",
    "- Photography and graphic design\n",
    "\n",
    "### Real-World Applications\n",
    "- **Instagram/Snapchat filters**: Brightness, contrast, saturation adjustments\n",
    "- **Medical imaging**: Enhancing X-rays and MRIs for better diagnosis\n",
    "- **Autonomous vehicles**: Processing camera feeds for object detection\n",
    "- **Satellite imagery**: Analyzing geographical data from aerial photos\n",
    "\n",
    "### Prerequisites Checklist\n",
    "- [ ] Completed Module 0: NumPy Refresher\n",
    "- [ ] Understand basic array creation and indexing\n",
