    "### 4.2 Operation 1: Brightness Adjustment\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mathematical Formulation:**\n",
    "\\[\n",
    "I_{\\text{bright}} = I_{\\text{original}} + \\Delta b\n",
    "\\]\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $\Delta b$ is the brightness adjustment (positive = brighter, negative = darker).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Constraints:** Pixel values must remain in [0, 255]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def adjust_brightness(image, delta):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Adjust image brightness by adding delta to all pixels.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    -----------\n",
    "    image : np.ndarray\n",
    "        Input grayscale image (2D array)\n",
    "    delta : int or float\n",
    "        Brightness adjustment value\n",
    "        \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    --------\n",
    "    np.ndarray\n",
    "        Brightness-adjusted image\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Convert to float to prevent overflow\n",
    "    adjusted = image.astype(np.float32) + delta\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Clip values to valid range [0, 255]\n",
    "    adjusted = np.clip(adjusted, 0, 255)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Convert back to uint8\n",
    "    return adjusted.astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test brightness adjustment\n",
    "bright_image = adjust_brightness(original_image, 50)\n",
    "dark_image = adjust_brightness(original_image, -50)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].imshow(original_image, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Original\\n(Mean: {:.1f})'.format(original_image.mean()), fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].imshow(bright_image, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Brightness +50\\n(Mean: {:.1f})'.format(bright_image.mean()), fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[2].imshow(dark_image, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=255)\n",
    "axes[2].set_title('Brightness -50\\n(Mean: {:.1f})'.format(dark_image.mean()), fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[2].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Brightness Adjustment Using Broadcasting', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold', y=1.02)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"‚úì Brightness adjustment complete\")\n",
    "print(f\"Original mean intensity: {original_image.mean():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Brightened mean intensity: {bright_image.mean():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Darkened mean intensity: {dark_image.mean():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Understanding Broadcasting:**\n",
    "\n",
    "When we do `image + 50`, NumPy broadcasts the scalar `50` across the entire 2D array:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Original:  [100, 150, 200]      Scalar: 50\n",
    "           [120, 180, 220]              ‚Üì\n",
    "                                      Broadcast\n",
    "           [100+50, 150+50, 200+50]   [150, 200, 250]\n",
    "Result: =  [120+50, 180+50, 220+50] = [170, 230, 270] ‚Üí [170, 230, 255] (clipped)\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
